user_question: What are the key differences between beach volleyball and indoor volleyball?
final_answer: Key differences between beach volleyball and indoor volleyball include the number of players (2 vs. 6), the playing surface (sand vs. hard court), the size of the court (smaller in beach volleyball), and the scoring system (rally scoring to 21 in beach vs. 25 in indoor).
